Description.
Size average for the genus (
Table 2
). Color: head with genae without distinct black pattern; pronotum folds with usually a light band edging the black band; hind femur with distinct shiny black longitudinal pattern on external (outer) field (
Fig. 23
). Male. 
Xth
abdominal tergite emargination as deep as wide (
Fig. 43
); paraprocts with a shirt wide projection (
Fig. 42
). Cercus dorsal lobe broadly rounded; median projection relatively short, bilobate (
Fig. 44–47
). Subgenital plate longer than wide; with indistinct emargination; styli separated by about styli length (
Fig. 41
). Titillators distal end pointing; internal part shaped as inverted wide Y (
Fig. 56
). File with ca. 42 teeth (
Fig. 30
). Female. Subgenital plate longer than wide, with V shaped emargination (
Fig. 60
). Ovipositor average for the genus, ventral margin with a relatively long strait area (
Fig. 61
, 
Table 2
).
